#True-Name Nemesis (#1085) choose-ONE witness - PARKED. After choosing the
#OPPONENT (choice 0), my own battlegrowth must still be able to target TNN.
#On master it cannot: the card's two mandatory `choice` auto-lines BOTH fire
#(merged may-must menu; after one fires the rest re-prompt and resolve), so
#TNN ends up with protection from BOTH players. Attempted fix (reverted): a
#single ability$! grant with _-separated choice modes - bare transforms and
#all(this) lose the source binding inside a player-grant (protection never
#lands); all(True-Name Nemesis|mybattlefield) anchors the transforms, but the
#second choice mode STILL fired (choose-one-of-N in grants is not single-
#fire). Engine fuel: grant-machinery rounds - single-fire choice menus +
#source binding for granted transforms.
[INIT]
firstmain
[PLAYER1]
manapool:{1}{U}{U}{G}
hand:true-name nemesis,battlegrowth
[PLAYER2]
[DO]
true-name nemesis
goto firstmain
goto firstmain
choice 0
goto firstmain
goto firstmain
battlegrowth
true-name nemesis
goto firstmain
goto firstmain
[ASSERT]
FIRSTMAIN
[PLAYER1]
graveyard:battlegrowth
inplay:true-name nemesis
[PLAYER2]
[END]
